JOHANNESBURG - The state capture inquiry has contacted the estranged wife of Malusi Gigaba, Norma Mngoma following her exclusive interview with eNCA where she alleged that the former Home Affairs Minister received bags of money from the Guptas. READ: Norma Mngoma dishes the dirt on Malusi Gigaba Meanwhile, the Public Protector's Office has made findings against Gigaba over the Guptas being granted early naturalisation certificates. While adverse findings have been made by the Public Protector, the office says, any remedial action taken against Gigaba would serve no judicial purpose, in light of his resignation as Home Affairs Minister.
